-- Saudi British Bank Reduces Fourth-Quarter Bad-Loan Provisions
-- B y   M o u r a d   H a r o u t u n i a n
-- 2012-02-13T08:40:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-13/saudi-british-bank-reduces-fourth-quarter-bad-loan-provisions.html
Saudi British Bank (SABB) , the lender 40
percent owned by  HSBC Holdings Plc (HSBA) , lowered provisions for bad
loans in the fourth quarter by almost two-thirds.  Provisions declined to 81.7 million riyals ($21.8 million)
in the three months ended Dec. 31, from 238.1 million riyals a
year earlier, according to data posted on the  Saudi bourse 
website today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mourad Haroutunian in Riyadh at 
